A 4 factor repeated-measures ANOVA was first conducted with Group as between-subject factor, and Instruction type, Food type and Response type as within-subject factors. To explore the relationship between RT and other dependent variables, we further reduced the number of within-subject factors related to RT by computing a “food attractiveness bias” (FAB) index as follows;\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
